ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I would absolutely recommend this course. I learned so much about storytelling of russian authors.
I would recommend this class. It wasn't too much work and Russian literature is really phenomenal. If your not familiar with it, this class is a great way to fix that.
I definitely recommend this for another student. Very interesting readings, and very helpful for writing skills (although it is not a writing credit which is unfortunate)
I would most definitely recommend this course to a fellow student. The reading list is fantastic, and you really feel you improve as a writer.
